question:
District category contains Wall Street, and Historic Downtown.
Supermarkets category contains Sam's Club, and Food 4 Less.
Product category contains Yogurt, and Iced Tea.
Ingredient category contains Cornmeal, and Saffron.
The number of each Historic Downtown 's Food 4 Less equals 11.
The number of each Wall Street 's Sam's Club equals 9 times each Sam's Club 's Yogurt.
The number of each Sam's Club 's Yogurt equals each Yogurt 's Saffron.
The number of each Iced Tea 's Cornmeal equals the difference of each Wall Street 's Ingredient and each Yogurt 's Saffron.
The number of each Yogurt 's Saffron equals each Historic Downtown 's Food 4 Less.
The number of each Food 4 Less 's Iced Tea equals 10 times the difference of each Sam's Club 's Yogurt and each Iced Tea 's Ingredient.
How many Cornmeal does Iced Tea have?
solution:
Define each Historic Downtown 's Food 4 Less as Y; So Y = 11.
Define each Yogurt 's Saffron as R; So R = Y = 11.
Define each Sam's Club 's Yogurt as p; So p = R = 11.
Define each Yogurt 's Ingredient as f; So f = R = 11.
Define each Wall Street 's Sam's Club as Q; So Q = 9 * p = 9 * 11 = 7.
Define each Sam's Club 's Ingredient as w; w = p * f = 11 * 11 = 6.
Define each Wall Street 's Ingredient as z; z = Q * w = 7 * 6 = 19.
Define each Iced Tea 's Cornmeal as F; So F = z - R = 19 - 11 = 8.
